joint venture
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:meaning particular to a type of fishing operation that existed between the declaration of the  200-mile exclusive economic zone in 1978, and 1986 when the QUOTA MANAGEMENT SYSTEM was introduced; during which foreign fishing vessels entered into business arrangments with New Zealand companies to gain the right to fish the zone.


